By the way, pray for Steve.

34:20.387 --> 34:23.151
He's running the Chicago Marathon next week.

34:23.691 --> 34:25.994
And so, hey, go, Steve, okay?

34:26.014 --> 34:26.735
We believe in you.

34:26.755 --> 34:28.137
Do a great job, okay?

34:28.157 --> 34:30.039
But his, he had no muscles.

34:30.360 --> 34:33.844
And now he gets up and he's dancing and leaping.

34:34.385 --> 34:37.869
That is a, how many of you have ever had your leg fall asleep?

34:39.511 --> 34:41.554
And then you get up and you try and walk.

34:42.594 --> 34:45.298
Imagine never walking.

34:46.560 --> 34:48.483
And now you're standing and you're leaping.

34:49.205 --> 34:51.428
That was a bonafide miracle.

34:51.869 --> 34:53.451
These guys were fishermen.

34:54.774 --> 34:58.339
And then they joined Jesus and they came out of that experience.

34:58.540 --> 34:59.201
And here's the deal.

34:59.782 --> 35:00.883
Fast forward one chapter.

35:00.903 --> 35:02.326
That was Acts chapter three.

35:02.366 --> 35:03.608
Go to Acts chapter four.

35:04.509 --> 35:09.938
P and John are arrested by the spiritual leaders of their day.

35:10.082 --> 35:12.905
who are not too happy with this whole Jesus movement thing.

35:13.646 --> 35:21.413
And they pulled Pete and John in and this is what they say, the members of the council were amazed when they saw the boldness of Peter and John.

35:21.834 --> 35:28.800
This is so key this phrase, for they could see that they were ordinary men with no special training in the scriptures.

35:29.401 --> 35:34.166
They also recognized them as men who had been with Jesus.

35:37.029 --> 35:38.450
Spending time with Jesus.

35:39.970 --> 35:40.932
It's a difference maker.

35:43.496 --> 35:47.323
Spend any time with Him alone dishewing Him.

35:48.926 --> 35:50.549
Out of that comes significance.

35:51.110 --> 35:52.512
Out of that comes purpose.

35:52.953 --> 35:54.356
Out of that comes power.

35:54.876 --> 35:56.379
Out of that comes meaning.

35:56.980 --> 36:01.388
Out of that comes deep soul satisfaction.

36:03.071 --> 36:04.754
So what does that look like for us today?

36:05.698 --> 36:13.950
Well, I think it probably, among other things, looks like us getting involved in maybe a life group or a learning group here at Heritage.

36:13.970 --> 36:16.915
It looks like connecting with someone that you respect spiritually.

36:17.616 --> 36:19.118
Maybe there's someone in your life that you know.

36:19.158 --> 36:29.654
It'd be awesome if they had 10 heritage, but whatever, I just, is there someone in your life that you know that you really respect spiritually and just getting together with them and asking them, how do you develop your relationship with Jesus?

36:31.236 --> 36:34.962
Getting around other guys or gals who are growing and just spending time with them.

36:35.458 --> 36:42.029
reading your Bible, starting in the New Testament of the Bible, picking a book like the book of James or the book of John.

36:42.070 --> 36:49.462
It's just beginning to read the Bible and asking the Holy Spirit, Holy Spirit, would you please open my eyes to the things you want me to see?

36:51.546 --> 36:57.016
All this is saying, make your relationship with Jesus a priority in your life.

36:58.859 --> 37:00.722
And Jesus said to his disciples one day,

37:00.930 --> 37:05.515
If any of you wants to be my follower, you must give up your own way, take up your cross and follow me.

37:06.276 --> 37:13.183
If you try to hang on to your life, if you try and keep doing everything you just kind of want to do, you're going to end up losing it.

37:13.203 --> 37:15.705
But if you give up your life for my sake, you'll save it.

37:16.846 --> 37:19.129
And what do you benefit if you gain the whole world?

37:20.510 --> 37:21.331
But lose your soul.

37:24.114 --> 37:28.018
So let me just ask you, and I know it's early on a Sunday morning, I get it.

37:29.602 --> 37:33.947
But I'm just asking what's distracting you from all that God has for you?

37:36.190 --> 37:37.552
Is it a league that you're in?

37:37.672 --> 37:38.553
Is it a hobby?

37:39.174 --> 37:40.195
Is it an activity?

37:40.315 --> 37:41.497
Is it a relationship?

37:46.262 --> 37:47.764
Is it a mindless activity?

37:53.071 --> 37:55.494
What's keeping you from all that God has for you?

37:57.957 --> 37:58.898
And number two,

37:59.682 --> 38:02.648
How are you limiting yourself from all that God has for you?

38:03.389 --> 38:04.551
What lies are you believing?

38:04.652 --> 38:05.573
Oh, I'm not good enough.

38:05.934 --> 38:06.796
I'm not smart enough.

38:06.876 --> 38:08.138
I don't know enough for the Bible.

38:08.178 --> 38:10.002
I'm not spiritual enough.

38:10.062 --> 38:11.124
I'm not talented enough.

38:11.845 --> 38:14.290
Too many people have what I call the Moses syndrome.

38:14.754 --> 38:22.221
In Exodus chapter three, in Exodus chapter four of the Old Testament of the Bible, God comes to Moses and he said, Mo, I want to use you to do amazing things.

38:22.542 --> 38:25.204
And Moses says four times over and over and over again.

38:25.224 --> 38:27.166
And he says, God, no, I'm not good enough.

38:27.246 --> 38:28.567
God, I can't talk right.

38:28.828 --> 38:30.689
God, I'm just not capable of doing this.

38:30.709 --> 38:33.772
And finally, you get to Exodus chapter four verse 13.

38:33.813 --> 38:38.397
Moses, again, for the fourth time he pleads, Lord, please send anyone else.

38:39.458 --> 38:43.602
Like anybody, God, that's how Moses started.

38:44.290 --> 38:53.699
But now fast forward and look at the new test from the Bible, Hebrews, Chapter 11, where he said it was by faith that Moses left the land of Egypt, not fearing the king's anger.

38:53.959 --> 38:57.543
He kept right on going because he kept his eyes on the one who's invisible.

38:57.923 --> 39:01.486
How does Moses go from saying, God choose anybody to God?

39:02.287 --> 39:03.308
Yes, I'll be used by you.

39:03.328 --> 39:03.829
You know how?

39:04.109 --> 39:08.673
He spent time with God, and God took care of the insecurity.

39:08.933 --> 39:13.778
God took care of any lack of ability, and God will do that in your life and my life.

39:15.106 --> 39:25.758
So here's the thing, you have no idea how many lives you will impact by simply following Jesus' invitations to follow him and let him guide you.

39:29.642 --> 39:32.805
So let me ask you one last time, two things.

39:33.726 --> 39:37.551
What's distracting you and what's limiting you?

39:38.812 --> 39:44.338
Because see, we've got a God who says to us, I want you to live life to

39:44.482 --> 39:45.704
The full.

39:47.646 --> 39:49.388
I don't want to take away from your life.

39:50.169 --> 39:56.618
I want you to live a full life, a meaningful life, a life filled with significance and purpose.

39:57.419 --> 40:09.554
I want you to know when you put your head down on the pillow that your life is actually heading in an awesome direction, that you're actually making a difference with your one and only life, that you're actually doing a great, great job.

40:09.634 --> 40:11.856
of living this life filled with purpose.

40:12.137 --> 40:20.586
You're Heavenly Father who cares about every detail of your life is saying to you, I care about you coming to a place where you know that's going on.

40:23.289 --> 40:31.238
So, what's distracting you and what's hindering you?

40:34.341 --> 40:34.962
I beg you.

40:38.818 --> 40:49.369
Allow the Holy Spirit to help you, to name the distractions, and to get rid of them.

40:49.389 --> 40:58.158
And to name the limitations that you put on your own life, and to the powerful Holy Spirit, to get rid of them.

41:00.020 --> 41:05.266
To say, I'm not gonna allow the things that come to my mind that tell me I can't, or I won't,

41:05.346 --> 41:13.897
or I tried in the past and I failed so I'm never going to reach it, allow those things to be obliterated by the Holy Spirit.

41:13.917 --> 41:17.162
Because God wants to do amazing things in and through you.

41:18.744 --> 41:23.310
I'm going to ask Pastor Jeremiah, and I just have to tell you, I'm such a fan of Pastor Jeremiah.

41:23.370 --> 41:24.151
I hope you are too.

41:24.672 --> 41:25.633
I just love this guy.

41:26.534 --> 41:27.756
So, Jeremiah, would you come?

41:28.277 --> 41:29.298
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

41:34.658 --> 41:42.508
I'm just going to ask him to lead us in a time of prayer, specifically around those two things and however Holy Spirit leads and guides him.

41:44.290 --> 41:49.297
But please, please don't limit what Holy Spirit wants to do in your life.

41:51.439 --> 41:52.941
This guy is an amazing guy.

41:54.243 --> 41:59.890
He loves Jesus, but can I tell you, God doesn't love Jeremiah one ounce more than he loves you.

42:02.274 --> 42:04.516
I got to tell you this one last thing and then I'll get off stage.

42:04.536 --> 42:07.499
I can't wait to introduce you to this friend of mine by the name of Dave Gary.

42:08.380 --> 42:09.401
Dave is in the marketplace.

42:11.303 --> 42:14.246
And Dave's done great, great things in the marketplace.

42:15.287 --> 42:19.432
I'm going to introduce you to him sometime before my interim time here at Heritage is done.

42:20.993 --> 42:23.316
Dave's daughter got married last night in Madison, Wisconsin.

42:23.416 --> 42:24.537
I was with them in Madison.

42:24.557 --> 42:25.618
I drove here late last night.

42:26.999 --> 42:29.522
And can I tell you?

42:30.050 --> 42:32.433
Dave is changing lives in the marketplace.

42:33.375 --> 42:41.106
So many people are coming to Jesus Christ in the marketplace just by him being a regular dude who has an anointing on his life in the marketplace.

42:41.807 --> 42:46.073
You don't have to be paid by a church to have significance and purpose.

42:46.734 --> 42:47.195
You don't.

42:47.996 --> 42:57.970
God has anointed some of you to be teachers and lawyers and factory workers and mechanics and stay at home moms

42:58.658 --> 43:01.362
And he wants to anoint you and powerfully use you.

43:01.642 --> 43:03.264
So please don't limit yourself.

43:03.685 --> 43:07.390
Please don't limit what you let God do in and through you.

43:08.411 --> 43:09.312
Would you guide us here?

43:09.332 --> 43:09.433
Yeah.

43:10.114 --> 43:11.055
Let's take just a moment.

43:11.075 --> 43:15.220
I'd encourage you to find a posture in prayer that is most comfortable for you.

43:16.082 --> 43:20.107
And we're just going to approach God's throne together.

43:20.768 --> 43:25.234
We do believe that the Word of God is alive and active, that

43:25.410 --> 43:27.212
Holy Spirit is speaking to us now.

43:27.452 --> 43:29.274
So we're just going to create some space.

43:29.294 --> 43:36.302
We're just going to cultivate some space, I should say, where we can interact around the things that we've just heard together.

43:36.883 --> 43:39.666
So let me lead us in this moment in space of prayer.

43:39.826 --> 43:40.587
Let's pray together.

43:42.990 --> 43:44.571
Father, Son, and Spirit.

43:46.414 --> 43:47.295
We are here.

43:47.535 --> 43:48.676
We exist.

43:48.836 --> 43:54.002
We are even in community in this space right now because of who you are.

43:55.682 --> 43:59.967
And so Lord, having heard your word, we don't want to move quickly beyond it.

44:00.047 --> 44:18.768
We don't want to be those who are like somebody who looks in a mirror and immediately forgets what they look like, but who interact with your word and see you reflected there, see ourselves there, and are changed by the power of your spirit at work through your living word.

44:20.269 --> 44:24.594
And so with my friends right now, Lord, we do ask you

44:26.050 --> 44:30.636
reveal to us where it is that we are distracted.

44:32.378 --> 44:44.393
Speak to us about the things that are distracting us from encountering the life of adventure and purpose of meaning that you have for us.

44:46.977 --> 44:54.386
And so we quiet our hearts and our minds before you and we ask Jesus, by your spirit, speak to us now.

45:02.306 --> 45:10.135
and friends as you are, as you're having ideas pop into mind thoughts that you didn't place there, but that are coming from God's own spirit.

45:11.136 --> 45:25.032
I encourage you ever so quietly, even where you are, to name those places of distraction for you, to bring them to the light, and they're in the light.

45:25.072 --> 45:26.834
They begin to lose their power.

45:41.474 --> 45:45.919
God, you have heard us name these spaces and places of distraction in our lives.

45:48.562 --> 45:50.184
We submit them to you.

45:50.224 --> 45:51.926
We lay them before you.

45:52.247 --> 45:57.593
God, these good things that you have given us that can distract us from greater things.

45:59.295 --> 46:08.946
And Lord, we pray that you would give us eyes that see what you are doing and hearts that long to be in that space of

46:09.314 --> 46:16.943
of purpose and adventure who are willing to lay these things aside, at least as we've been using them and press into something more.

46:18.385 --> 46:38.450
And now we ask you, Holy Spirit, would you reveal to us how we have been limiting ourselves, the spaces, the lies, the words that we have used to limit ourselves and say, I can't possibly step into that thing or live in that way because Lord, you've heard that.

46:38.882 --> 46:40.664
that monologue in our own minds and hearts.

46:40.684 --> 46:41.946
So reveal that to us now.

46:56.606 --> 47:08.882
And again, friends, I invite you to take the courageous step of also quietly right where you are naming some of those spaces of limitation, because again,

47:09.154 --> 47:12.237
and bringing them to the light, they begin to lose their power.

47:24.049 --> 47:32.817
Your word, O God, tells us that you are able to do exceedingly and abundantly beyond all that we could ask or imagine.

47:34.519 --> 47:37.682
So with my brothers and sisters in this place, again, God, we

47:37.762 --> 47:39.705
lay these things down before you.

47:40.626 --> 47:50.659
We ask you to help remind us when we are choosing limitation over the limitless opportunity that you have before us.

47:53.163 --> 47:59.792
Lord, where those limitations are coming out of deep wounding, I pray that you would heal our hearts, our minds, our souls.

48:01.074 --> 48:07.282
Where we've bought into lies about what we are able to be and do that are so small.

48:08.130 --> 48:11.214
I pray that the truth of your spirit and your word would free us.

48:13.537 --> 48:22.808
God, that my friends, this family together, that we would be found faithful in living into far beyond all we could even ask or imagine.

48:23.309 --> 48:29.536
Not for our sake, not for our fame, but for the glory of your great name alone.

48:30.237 --> 48:37.426
We ask all these things in trust and expectancy with you, in Jesus' name.

48:57.698 --> 49:00.187
we could ever see.

49:03.097 --> 49:06.770
Were they of all the praise we could ever breathe?

49:33.858 --> 49:42.994
Worthy of every breath we could ever breathe we live for you

58:43.586 --> 58:46.609
so much for joining with us for worship today.

58:46.649 --> 58:56.599
If you would like to pray with a pastor or just want more information about the church in general, please go to heritageqc.com slash connect.

58:58.261 --> 59:08.210
We also know that God loves the heart of a cheerful giver and your radical generosity enables us to better show love to our congregation and to our community.

59:09.211 --> 59:11.794
So if you would like to take a moment and give

59:12.450 --> 59:17.971
You can do that through the website at heritageqc.com slash giz or through the church center app.

59:19.758 --> 59:22.930
Again, thanks for joining us for worship and we'll see you next week.

